<br>
BTW, I don't really care to see folks reselling bags I've clicked for 'em so it's not free except to those that have helped me out in the past on various things.  Here some examples of deals for bags I'll do:<br>
<br>
10K plat to buy one outright.<br>
5K plat + 36 tufts + 3 BDs, success guarenteed.<br>
72 tufts + 6 BDs, success guarenteed.<br>
<br>
For the budget concious, I'll do minimum tufts + BDs + wires + 2K click fee.  The fee covers as many clicks as needed for the subcomines (you supply parts -- 48+5 should cover it with leftovers likely for you to keep) and one click for the final bag.  Fee is not refunded on bag failure, but that's unlikely.<br>
<br>
For those that think this is expensive, you're right.  IMHO, unless alot of people start taking me up on the 72+6 deal or the bazaar starts stocking tufts in wholesale quantities, the foraging time required is just plain too outrageous to charge less.  So, I really don't expect anyone but monks and perhaps foraging classes to take me up on this.  For non-monks that can't forage, I'd highly recommend the tinkerer's bag.  It's 5250p from a vendor in sol-a: wt 1.0 100% 10-slot.<br>
<br>
Background on the combines: <br>
<br>
36 Tufts of Dire Wolf Fur (foraged in most vellious zones, ~5p baz) <br>
03 Blue Diamonds (dropped various spots, ~500p baz) <br>
03 Platinum Threads (storebought, 210p) <br>
01 Misty Acorn / Misty Acorn Oil (foraged in misty thicket only, ~2-25p baz)<br>
<br>
There's always a 5% chance of failure and with 22+ subcombines there's sure to be at least one that eats some tufts or BDs.  A tuft failure will chew up 3 or 9 tufts depending on which fails.  The chance of a perfect run on the subcombines is ~33% and never gets any better with higher skill. Wrye is 13:14 on the final sack.<br>
<br>
Note that the final combine is not trivial for Wrye, but it was close enough for me to risk my own parts. The EQTC failure rate formula for 217+5% implies that she should expect a 90% success rate on the final combine and 95% success on all the subcombines (all subs are trivial). She's currently 93% on bags.<br>
<br>
Average time to forage 36 tufts at 200+15% foraging skill is about 4 hours.  I've heard a rumor that they drop from dire wolves, too.  I've not confirmed this myself.  They can be foraged in most Vellious zones.<br>
<br>
